    "libertarianNote": "The original justified war — fighting for self-governance and individual liberty against imperial taxation without representation. Yet the Founders immediately created a government that would tax, conscript, suppress rebellions (Whiskey Rebellion), and expand westward through force. Even the 'good war' led to government power the revolutionaries would have recognized as tyrannical. The tree of liberty required refreshing after just 11 years.",
    "objectives": [
      "Independence from Britain",
      "Self-governance"
    ],
    "objectivesMet": true,
    "computed": {
      "durationYears": 8,
