        "note": "Imprisoned for four months under the Sedition Act for criticizing Adams, becoming a martyr for free speech. Won reelection from his jail cell, proving that persecution could backfire politically."
      },
      {
        "name": "Timothy Pickering",
        "role": "Secretary of State",
        "note": "Hamilton's ally who opposed Adams's peace initiatives and worked to sabotage diplomatic negotiations. Represented the ultra-Federalist faction that preferred war to compromise."
      },
      {
        "name": "George Logan",
